,Recommended,270270,32065417,Posted: 30 May,all,Depleted Residual Material,"A complex and hard survival horror game with pretty sophisticated crafting system, huge random loot diversity and interesting horror settings. However serious gameplay flaws related to akward camera controls and clunky melee combat mechanics (but not as tragically bad as many revievers say) can make the game unnecessarily difficult at some moments. ""Large open world"" as stated in the official description is a little misleading because the province where you are placed in is in fact devided into rather small self contained locations (which vary in their size and of course the scenery) accessible only via map fast travel or special transit zones initiating new level loading. One thing I personally dislike cuz it makes the game feel unbaked despite of fact it left Early Access a few months ago is the lack of character appearance customisation - it doesn't matter you wear a warm coat and ushanka or a light jacket with winter mask and backpack, you always look the same.Despite its flaws I still recommend this title mainly because it has a great post-apocalyptic atmosphere in winter scenery and really terrifying otherworldly foes. If you are ""The Thing"" movie/game and S.T.A.L.K.E.R. series fan  then you should feel at home while playing ""Frozen State""."
