76561198102302636,Recommended,270270,11387134,"Posted: 24 July, 2014",all,bbaileyn7,"I can understand if people are nervous about paying for an Alpha game, however few alpha games are as good in there early states as this one. This is an Alpha game that has tremendous content very early on.It is a survival game but very few games make winter an enemy. Cold weather can kill you if your not paying attention to your temperture and if you decide to take on a hybrid, (the current enemy in the game) you have to be fast because some will kill you without thinking about it. This game is not a complete rougelike but if you die, you restart, and about ninety percent of the items and objects are procedural generated. Plus (as I said above) the enemies are as deadly as the weather itself.Now the game is early so it has it's fair share of bugs, but from my experience I didn't come across any game breaking bugs and I play this game on a laptop with an Intel hd graphics 4000 (I did have to reduce some graphic settings). There's not much that I dislike about this game, the enemies are done right so far, keeping track of your characters health (food, water, etc..) isn't too bad, and having the random generation changes things up a bit.The issues that I do have, is that there is no sprint button. So it takes a while to do certain things such as gathering wood to build your cabin. There's no map, so it's very easy to get lost if you don't keep track of what your doing. Also there's only three enemy types and there's only one that I try to avoid (fortunately more are going to be added soon). Besides that there isn't anything else that bothers me, I would highly recommend you try this. The Developer is very nice and he listens to people on the forums. Most devs don't do that. :)"
