76561197988927906,Not Recommended,270270,12967584,"Posted: 16 November, 2014",all,BloodPanda,"Not yet, this game has some very glowing reviews but let me be the first to say that they are undeserved praises, this game is no masterpiece and it certainly isn't good enough yet to warrant such praise as others have slathered upon it.As you can see by my time played I have only roughly 1 hour of gameplay, that is simply because the controls are so damn clunky that I can hardly stand to play it any longer. While I am no big fan of top down games in the first place this one offers a very interesting feel and has much potential, but, the WASD-E interact setup is lost on top down and only served to make the controls unbearably inefficient, the game would benefit from the option to change controls from their original setting to a user preferred setting. (allow me to set key bindings)Another issue I found currently is that the max range of interaction is too low, if I light a campfire I end up being burned because I have to practically stand inside the fire to interact with it. Your characters movements are rough and choppy and hiding, while a neat game mechanic, is not implemented well at this point since the interactions are still in poor repair...trying to hide in a wardrobe when a gross mutated monster is chasing you takes a while since you have to find that interaction sweet spot just to get into the wardrobe.So, cons - Clunky, offputting controls. Poor interaction mechanics. Great music, poor atmospheric sounds. Top-down ruins the atmosphere, Choppy movements...and let me add, poorly constructed ""inventory"" screen...listing items? drag and drop? I feel as though I stepped back into 1999.Pros - Survival game, if you like survival games then keep your eyes on this one. Wonderful list of lootables and craftables. Can run on low-end machines since it is graphically simplistic.Ultimately I cannot recommend this to hardcore survival gaming fans as it does not really deliver satisfying game play and the survival mechanics are rough at best, starving and needing to eat in just 6 hours? Dying of thirst after half a day?  I am constantly having to drink and eat and burn myself on a campfire to stay warm.So, kids...don't waste your money yet unless you have $10 you don't mind spending...it isn't terrible but it certainly isn't what the other comments make it out to be."
